INTERVIEW QUESTION:
1)WHAT IS IFRAME AND WHAT ARE THE METHODS OF IFRAME?
--> Html inside of another html.People use iframe to make sure they can give more protection for the specific data(advertisement,videos)
    a)driver.switchTo.frame(WebElement);
    b)driver.switchTo.frame(index);
    c)driver.switchTo.frame(id or name );*****
2)How do you find all the iframe in the DOM? // how do you find all the links in the DOM
-->//iframe or //frame
-->//a
***3)How do you go to the main HTML?
-->driver.switchTo().defaultContent();
4)How do you go to the upper HTML?
-->driver.switchTo().Parentframe();
5)What will happen if you do not switch to the frame and sendKeys?
-->NoSuchElement Exception.
6)What will happen if you try to switch to the frame which is not exist?
-->NoSuchFrameException
ALERT/POPups:
*Operation System Alert(OS pop up)--> We cannot handle OS alert using selenium
  NOTE:Solution for this might be using ROBOT class. :)
**HTML pop-ups--> We can find the element for the pop up and click/close it.
**JavaScript pop-up-->We should use ALERT class to handle the javascript.This class
has 4 methods to handle the alerts
Alert interview Questions:
1)how do you handle the alert in Selenium:
-->If it is coming from HTML-->i just find the element and click/close it
-->If it is coming from OS-->you cannot handle it in selenium
-->if it is coming from JavaScript-->I need to use ALERT CLASS.
2)How many different ways we can handle the JSalert?
-->accept-->it clicks 'OK' button
-->dismiss-->it clicks 'Cancel' button
-->senKeys-->it sends the input to the alert pop-up
-->GetText-->it gets the text of pop-up.
3)Is Alert class or interface?
--> Alert is a class.
4)If you do not handle the alerts(pop-ups), what kind of exception do you get?
--> UnhandledAlertException